UID:6GCZ6AyqTueuLOkaeN4uZ
SUMMARY:Chamber 101
DTSTAMP:20260326T215657Z
DTSTART:20260408T223000Z
DESCRIPTION:Chamber 101: An Introduction to Your Local Chamber of Commerce 
	Chamber 101 is an informative and engaging session designed to help member
	s\, prospective members\, and community partners understand what the Chamb
	er of Commerce is\, how it operates\, and how it supports local businesses
	. During this event\, attendees will learn: What a Chamber of Commerce is 
	and the role it plays in strengthening the local business ecosystem. What 
	the Chamber does\, including advocacy\, networking\, business development\
	, community partnerships\, and economic growth initiatives. How membership
	 works\, what benefits are available\, and how to make the most of the res
	ources\, programs\, and visibility opportunities offered by the Chamber. W
	ays to get involved\, from attending events and committees to leveraging p
	romotional tools and support services. Chamber 101 is ideal for anyone loo
	king to better understand how the Chamber supports business success and ho
	w to fully engage with its mission and network. This session provides a we
	lcoming space to ask questions\, meet Chamber staff\, and connect with fel
	low community members.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/ch
	amber-101/17665198/2026-04-08T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/chamber-101/17665198/2026
	-04-08T00
LOCATION:Chamber Office\, 3100 S 176th St\, SeaTac\, WA
